[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mansfield Town: Jimmy Spencer, Paul Digby & Paul Anderson join League Two club

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Mansfield have signed Plymouth striker Jimmy Spencer, former England under-20 international Paul Digby and ex-Nottingham Forest winger Paul Anderson.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Former Notts County forward Spencer, 25, will officially join when his contract runs out on 1 July.
Digby, 22, who plays in defence or midfield, joined Ipswich Town in January 2016 but only played 12 games.
Anderson, 28, left Northampton earlier this month following a year-long spell at the League One club.
The length of the trio's contracts have not been revealed.
